Titre du poste : Senior Project Manager/Gestionnaire de projet 

À propos de l’offre d’emploi
A Snapshot of Your Day

Are you a professional, dynamic individual with experience in managing FACTs and Substations projects? Do you seek to make a meaningful difference in people's lives? Then you have chosen the right place to work.

As Senior Project Manager you are planning, driving, and closing projects, ensuring they are completed on time, within budget, and meeting quality standards. You collaborate with our cross-functional team, handle resources, identify risks, and communicate progress to partners and stakeholders, ultimately driving projects to successful completion.

How You’ll Make An Impact

Your tasks as the Senior Project Manager include planning the activities and resources, organizing and motivating the project team (including Sub Project Managers), controlling time management and costs, analyzing and managing risks, and ensuring customer satisfaction.
Design, develop and manage customer projects, according to defined Siemens Energy Project Management (PM) standards and customer requirements, and with responsibility for economic results.
You will bear the responsibility for reporting of the progress of the project. Involvement in the project in offering phase supporting the sales by defining deliverables, finding subcontractors, budgeting etc. gives you variation to the site routines. You will be part of execution team as a key leader.
Schedule Management – Lead the project management team in monitoring and maintaining the project schedule(s). Attend schedule meetings as required.
Lead the project management team in producing the required deliverables, both internally and externally. Assure deliverables / reports are produced in the frequencies described in the contract documents.
Change Management – Understand the change management processes as they apply to each specific contract on the project. Be able to disseminate and explain the processes to other members of the project management team. Be able to produce reports – including Change Order Logs.


